Bestiary.Gerson: An ancient tortoise who has already completed his journey. He offers guidance to those seeking to understand their inner nature.

Dialogue: {
	Gerson: {
		NoTrait1: Gya ha ha! I see you have not yet discovered your soul trait. Care to choose? Or perhaps you're looking to challenge yourself?
		NoTrait2: Every soul has a trait that defines them. What might yours be, I wonder?
		NoTrait3: The soul is a curious thing. Let me help you find yours.
		HasTrait1: Ah, I see your soul shines bright. But remember, you can always change your path... until the next chapter.
		HasTrait2: Your soul trait serves you well! Or perhaps you wish to try another?
		Locked1: The next chapter has arrived, and your story has begun. Your trait is now set in stone.
		Locked2: Once the next chapter has arrived, there is no going back. Your soul has chosen its path.
		General1: My story has come to it's end. Now, it's your turn!
		General2: You want me to help you fight? Nah, that would be too easy for you!
		ChooseTrait: Soul Traits
		ViewTrait: View Trait
		TraitInfo: Your soul radiates with {0}. This path is now permanent.
		Traits: Traits
		Help: Help
		Dialogue: Dialogue
		SelectTrait: Select Trait
		Back: Back
		Next: Next
		Close: Close
		HelpPreSkeletron1: I'm too old to be fightin' along side ya, but I've got a few things that could help!
		HelpPreSkeletron2: I can help unlock the potential of your SOUL! I'll provide some basic equipment, but the rest is on you!
		HelpPreSkeletron3: Once the dungeon's cleared of all that nasty curse junk, I can get you some weapons, too!
		HelpPreHardmode1: Nice job clearing out the Dungeon! I've got some weapons stocked up. They'll serve you well as you prepare for the next chapter.
		HelpPreHardmode2: But be warned... once the spirits of Light and Dark are released, I can't change your SOUL's trait anymore.
		HelpPostHardmode1: You're onto the next chapter. I knew you had it in you! If you're here to change your soul trait, I'm sorry to say I can't anymore.
		HelpPostHardmode2: While you were down there fighting that meat rectangle, someone stopped by and gave me this Game Controller-a thingy. Seems like they wanted you to have it.
		HelpPostHardmode3: Now, I don't know much about games, but I'd be careful. Seems like there's more to it than meets the eye.
		HelpPostERAM1: Looks like ya beat the game! Technology is so advanced these days...
	}
}

